# Project context for Claude Code

> Pointer file. Real context lives in `AGENTS.md` and `.ai-factory/`.
>
> **Authoritative for:** Claude Code session-load pointer format directing agents to `AGENTS.md` / `.ai-factory/`.
> **NOT authoritative for:** project goal — see consumer's README.md.

This project follows the AGENTS.md standard. Claude Code reads BOTH this file AND `AGENTS.md` at session start. To avoid drift between them, this file contains no rules — only pointers.

## Source of truth

- **`AGENTS.md`** — what we're building, workflow, slim list of rules
- **`.ai-factory/DESCRIPTION.md`** — stack, hard constraints, non-goals
- **`.ai-factory/ARCHITECTURE.md`** — layer rules, dependency direction
- **`.ai-factory/RULES.md`** — code rules R1–R20 (enforced)

## Workflow

Before every commit / PR, run the gate this installer ships (unconditional — needs no extra install):

- `./scripts/audit-ai-docs.sh` — drift + code-vs-docs probes.
- the pre-push hook (`.husky/pre-push`) fires on `git push` (typecheck, `vitest related`, dependency-cruiser).
- CI gates the PR (`ci-success` required check) — the last-resort authority, independent of local tooling.

**If you use AI Factory (aif)** (not bundled by this installer) for non-trivial changes:

- `/aif-plan <task>` — plan + branch
- `/aif-implement` — execute step-by-step
- `/aif-verify` — _if you use aif_, runs sub-agents over RULES.md + the audit-ai-docs probes. A convenience wrapper around the gate above, not a substitute for it.
- `/aif-fix <error>` — targeted fix
- `/aif-commit` — final commit

Don't bypass the pre-push hook / `./scripts/audit-ai-docs.sh` with `--no-verify`. If a rule is incompatible with the task — discuss it, don't silently skip.

## What NOT to put here

- Code style → ESLint/Prettier configs
- Test conventions → `RULES.md` R4 + `audit-ai-docs.sh`
- Architectural rules → `dependency-cruiser` + `RULES.md` R3
- Project description → `AGENTS.md` + `.ai-factory/DESCRIPTION.md`

`CLAUDE.md` is a pointer. Real rules are enforced, not described.
